title: Romeo Jumpstarts Countdown To Comeback With Individual Teaser Images For “Without U”
text:
Boy group Romeo has finally unveiled something for their upcoming comeback! 
On February 24, their agency released individual teaser photos for each of the members, and revealed that their fourth mini album will be titled “Without U.” While supposed news of a February comeback has been circulating amongst fans since December 2016, these photos mark a countdown to an actual comeback date, which as yet to be announced. 
In the unique photos, the members are out of focus, and other items such as a picture frame with a group photo, a mirror, and a poster are in focus instead. They appear to be in a dimly-lit classroom, but are dressed in casual everyday clothing as opposed to uniforms. 
Romeo debuted in May 2015 under CT Entertainment with their extended play, “The Romeo,” and their most recent mini album was around six months ago with “First Love,” a repackage of mini album “Miro.” 
Are you excited for their return?
